The paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network (CNN) classifier model for automatic modulation classification (AMC) under realistic wireless channel impairments. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information theory and communication (cs.IT) as it discusses the classification of modulation classes. The use of deep learning (DL) methods also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset for testing and evaluation, which may suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
